      "message": "It strikes me as weird that this method is bound to a link using `on-tap`, when the link already does something when tapped.\n\nI\u0027m guessing the underlying cause of issue 5932 is the way the browser emulates tap events from a clicks. This method worked when the user clicks because the tap is emulated after the link is handled. But when the user actually taps, the order is reversed and the `on-tap` is run before the native link tap handler.\n\nIt seems like a mistake to double-bind to an event in a way that depends on such subtleties of the order of invocation. (It also feels wrong to double-bind in general.)\n\nIf you tap another file in the file dropdown, that should cause the gr-diff-view to reload, right? What if, instead of the extra binding, the gr-diff-view always closes the dropdown when it\u0027s reloaded?\n\nAnother approach would be to bind _handleFileTap to the capture phase of the tap, but I believe this cannot be done using a regular Polymer binding.",
